Now modify the filter values

You need retype to int and then retype to string. Because..&lt;br&gt;
- you are using `Enum.GetNames` which return string values instead of int.&lt;br&gt;
- parse name into enum value and retype to int and then to string because SelectListItem.Value need string as value.&lt;br&gt;

So you need something like this

    var roles = Enum.GetNames(typeof(Gender))
                    .Where(f =&gt; f != Gender.Others.ToString())
                    .Select(f =&gt; new SelectListItem { Value = ((int) Enum.Parse&lt;Gender&gt;(f)).ToString(), Text = f }).ToList();

Option two

You can use `GetValues` instead of `GetNames`

    var roles2 = ((Gender[]) Enum.GetValues(typeof(Gender))).ToList()
                    .Where(f =&gt; f.ToString() != Gender.Others.ToString())
