answers.body_markdown:
The declaration

     int num= 1234, r;

is shorthand for

     int num= 1234;
     int r;
It does not assign `r` to `1234`, you cannot change the value of numbers in C#.

The prefix operator `+` is not particularly useful, as it just means &#39;keep the current sign&#39;, in this case `+r` does not have any different effect to writing `r` by itself.

